                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>/8–1948:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Belgium</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-21T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 21, 1948—3 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1260. For your further background <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 1604
                    Aug 19 in personal discussion we hope you can have with Bech and possibly
                    further talks Bel <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>, Dept has following
                    comments re de Gruben’s observations. Normally Neth might well be considered
                    best qualified candidate. Under present circumstances, however, Dept questions
                    whether it would really be to her best interests to stand, and if she stood if
                    she could be elected. Hence Dept believes any suggestions possibility Neth
                    candidacy should be discreetly discouraged.</p>
                <p>Dept surprised de Gruben’s comment re possibility area giving up seat. Dept feels
                    under present circumstances would not be desirable for area and not in U.S.
                    interests. We had thought all Western and Northern European states shared this
                    opinion. Even staff member Swedish Del New York spoke strongly on it to US
                    Del.</p>
                <p>If possible obtain more official statement Bel attitude prior Spaak’s return
                    would be most helpful to Dept.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
